122: /* Interface for classes applying changes to request state/RADOS store
123:  * imposed by a particular rgw::auth::Engine.
124:  *
125:  * In contrast to rgw::auth::Engine, implementations of this interface
126:  * are allowed to handle req_state or RGWUserCtl in the read-write manner.
127:  *
128:  * It's expected that most (if not all) of implementations will also
129:  * conform to rgw::auth::Identity interface to provide authorization
130:  * policy (ACLs, account's ownership and entitlement). */
131: class IdentityApplier : public Identity {
132: public:
133:   typedef std::unique_ptr<IdentityApplier> aplptr_t;
134: 
135:   virtual ~IdentityApplier() {};
136: 
137:   /* Fill provided RGWUserInfo with information about the account that
138:    * RGWOp will operate on. Errors are handled solely through exceptions.
